description:
&lt;p&gt;This exciting role will form part of the team that makes up the National Incident Coordination Centre (NICC) for the Public Health COVID-19 team which is being established to ensure PHE continues to lead an effective and resilient response to the coronavirus pandemic and any associated winter and other additional predictable pressures on the health, care and public health systems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post will be fixed term for 12 months (with potential to extend for a further 6 months) and the successful applicant will be based at Wellington House, London.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The purpose of this post is to provide specialist Emergency Preparedness, Resilience and Response (EPRR) operational management support to the COVID-19 NICC and to develop and maintain national and regional preparedness, resilience and response guidance, plans, training and exercise programs to enable PHE to maintain an effective and timely response to COVID-19, in conjunction with our partner agencies and stakeholders.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post involves a high degree of autonomy and requires regular operational level decision making on a wide range of managerial topics.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be directly line managed by and professionally accountable to the Lead EPRR Manager.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants should have office management experience as well as proven experience in delivery of EPRR operations or response outcomes. Extensive experience of handling and processing complex and sensitive information is essential, as is the ability to negotiate and communicate with senior management, partner agencies and key stakeholders on difficult or controversial issues.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The attached job description gives an indication of the types of activities that might be expected from this role but is not specific for this post. The responsibilities for this post will be focused on the COVID-19 activities carried out by the NICC and may be subject to change in order for PHE to rapidly adapt, and dynamically respond, to COVID-19.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please ensure you set out how you meet the essential criteria highlighted in the job description within your application.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Option 3 – External&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Open to all external applicants (anyone) from outside the Civil Service (including by definition internal applicants).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
